| The brain           | The brain. Capable of so much, the most complex object in the world. Thoughts, problem-solving, speech, art, music all began their journeys in a brain much like yours. Since our focus is writing, the question that must be answered is WHAT IS A WRITING BRAIN? |
|                     | Neurologically speaking, the brain's plasticity requires repetition - in the form of practice, and simulation - to mould itself for an activity or the other. Think of your favourite musician - they have probably spent hours honing their skills, and their minds, for that activity. Writing is no different. |
